  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What should I do to make my crush notice me?",
  "response": "Making your crush notice you can be exciting and nerve-wracking, but it\u2019s important to stay authentic and confident. Here are some thoughtful and effective tips to help you grab their attention:\n\n### 1. **Be Yourself**\n   - Authenticity is key. Don\u2019t try to be someone you\u2019re not just to impress them. Let them see the real you.\n\n### 2. **Build Confidence**\n   - Confidence is attractive. Work on your self-esteem, stand tall, and embrace your strengths.\n\n### 3. **Engage in Conversation**\n   - Start small by saying hello or asking about their day. Find common interests to talk about, like shared hobbies, music, or classes.\n\n### 4. **Be Present**\n   - Spend time around them naturally, whether at school, work, or social events. Be friendly and approachable.\n\n### 5. **Show Genuine Interest**\n   - Ask questions about their passions and listen actively. People notice when you\u2019re genuinely interested in what they care about.\n\n### 6. **Use Body Language**\n   - Smile, make eye contact, and face them when talking. Positive body language can make you more approachable.\n\n### 7. **Be Kind and Thoughtful**\n   - Small gestures, like a kind word or a thoughtful compliment, can leave a lasting impression.\n\n### 8. **Be Active on Social Media**\n   - Like or comment on their posts occasionally, but don\u2019t overdo it. Keep it light and friendly.\n\n### 9. **Find Common Ground**\n   - Join activities or groups they\u2019re involved in to spend more time together naturally.\n\n### 10. **Be Patient**\n   - Building a connection takes time. Don\u2019t rush things or force interactions. Let things develop naturally.\n\n### 11. **Work on Your Own Goals**\n   - Focus on your passions and hobbies. Being passionate about something can make you more intriguing.\n\n### 12. **Be Approachable**\n   - Stay open and friendly with others, not just your crush. This makes you seem sociable and welcoming.\n\n### 13. **Give Them Space**\n   - Don\u2019t overdo the attention. Give them room to breathe and come to you naturally.\n\n### 14. **Ask for Help or Advice**\n   - If you share a class or interest, ask for their help or opinion on something. This can spark a conversation.\n\n### 15. **Be Positive**\n   - A positive attitude is contagious. People are drawn to those who radiate good energy.\n\nRemember, the goal isn\u2019t to change who you are but to let your crush see the best version of yourself. If they don\u2019t notice you, it\u2019s okay\u2014it\u2019s their loss, and someone else will appreciate you for who you are. Good luck! \ud83d\ude0a",
  "temperature": 1.0,
